{"type":"message","id":"31f6b9ce","parentId":"7410d3d5","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:21:35.058Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_uibn1vui5ekp_1","toolName":"process","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[LLM] response length: 4326\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='research/STRATEGY_C_EXPERIMENT.md' new_len=1388\r\n[mutation proposed] research/STRATEGY_C_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n[master 703790c] pulse: 2026-03-24 142114\n 6 files changed, 245 insertions(+), 83 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 142114.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 142114.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-24 142016.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 142114 - The CFI compression experiment revealed that binary thresholds fail because constant-format tokens (freq�160, CFI=1) look causal but carry zero information. The hybrid scoring formula is ready but not yet tested.\n\nProcess exited with code 0."}],"details":{"status":"completed","sessionId":"keen-kelp","exitCode":0,"aggregated":"[LLM] response length: 4326\r\n[mutation parsed via Python] old='(new file)' file='research/STRATEGY_C_EXPERIMENT.md' new_len=1388\r\n[mutation proposed] research/STRATEGY_C_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n[master 703790c] pulse: 2026-03-24 142114\n 6 files changed, 245 insertions(+), 83 deletions(-)\n create mode 100644 memory/session/pulse_2026-03-24 142114.md\n create mode 100644 mutations/proposed/2026-03-24 142114.mutation\n rename mutations/{proposed => rejected}/2026-03-24 142016.mutation (100%)\n[sandbox pulse] 2026-03-24 142114 - The CFI compression experiment revealed that binary thresholds fail because constant-format tokens (freq�160, CFI=1) look causal but carry zero information. The hybrid scoring formula is ready but not yet tested.\r\n","name":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774376495057}}
{"type":"message","id":"3927484a","parentId":"31f6b9ce","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:21:35.060Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_uibn1vui5ekp_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 142016\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: the (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me review the current state and what needs to be done next.\r\n\r\nFrom the goals:\r\n- Phase 1 COMPLETE: Architecture cross-analysis + integration spec synthesized\r\n- Pending: Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n  - Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n  - Test: does this distinguish \"constant format\" (freq≈160, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<120, CFI>0.5)?\r\n  - Run: 200 pulses, 80/20 split, compare against binary thresholds\r\n\r\nKey insights:\r\n1. CFI and frequency are ORTHOGONAL signals\r\n2. Constant-format tokens (freq=160, CFI=1) are the trap\r\n3. Three-dimensional compression filter: CFI ≥ 0.5 AND freq ≥ 3 AND freq < 120\r\n4. Compression objective for Layer 1 is now concrete: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n\r\nThe next action is to run the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C). This involves:\r\n1. Implementing the scoring formula: score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n2. Running 200 pulses with 80/20 split\r\n3. Comparing against binary thresholds\r\n\r\nLooking at the previous CFI compression experiment in `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md`, I should design and implement the hybrid experiment now.\r\n\r\nLet me create the experiment script or document for Strategy C.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe next concrete step is the Hybrid CFI×Freq scoring experiment (Strategy C) using score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120). This formula should distinguish constant-format tokens (freq≈160, CFI=1, score=1.0) from research trajectory tokens (freq<120, CFI>0.5, score<0.5).\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate the Strategy C experiment script that implements the hybrid scoring formula and runs the 200-pulse comparison against binary thresholds.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Strategy C: Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment\r\n## 2026-03-24\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nThe formula `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` will:\r\n- Penalize constant-format tokens (freq=160, CFI=1 → score=1.0 but capped at 1.0)\r\n- Reward research trajectory tokens (freq<120, CFI>0.5 → score<0.5)\r\n- Distinguish \"appears in every pulse\" from \"causally connected\"\r\n\r\n## Key Distinction\r\n| Token | freq | CFI | Binary CFI≥0.5 | Hybrid Score |\r\n|-------|------|-----|----------------|--------------|\r\n| \"for next instantiation\" | 160 | 1.00 | TRUE (bad) | 1.00 |\r\n| \"pulse\" | 160 | 1.00 | TRUE (bad) | 1.00 |\r\n| \"Phase 1\" | 136 | 0.96 | TRUE (bad) | 0.96 |\r\n| \"architecture\" | 80 | 0.60 | TRUE (good) | 0.40 |\r\n| \"temporal\" | 40 | 0.70 | TRUE (good) | 0.23 |\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n- Pulses: 200 (160 train / 40 test)\r\n- Split: 80/20\r\n- Compare: Hybrid scoring vs Binary CFI≥0.5 vs Binary CFI≥0.7\r\n- Metric: Precision/Recall on research-relevant tokens\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\n```\r\ndef hybrid_score(cfi, freq):\r\n    return cfi * min(1.0, freq / 120)\r\n\r\ndef is_research_token(token_data):\r\n    cfi, freq = token_data['cfi'], token_data['freq']\r\n    score = hybrid_score(cfi, freq)\r\n    return score >= 0.25  # Threshold tuned for hybrid\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Expected Outcome\r\n- Hybrid will have precision ≈ CFI-hard (high signal)\r\n- Hybrid will have recall > CFI-hard (captures research trajectory)\r\n- Key: \"Phase 1\" (score=0.96) still scores high - it's truly causal\r\n- Key: \"for next\" (score=1.00) scores high but SHOULD be filtered by post-processing\r\n- Combined filter: hybrid_score > 0.25 AND freq >= 3\r\n```\r\nfile: research/STRATEGY_C_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 14:20:35\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774376495058}}
